        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Prove <xref ref="th_matrixscale_dist2"/>.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Prove <xref ref="th_matrixscale_assoc"/>.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Prove <xref ref="th_matrixscale_assoc"/>.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </statement>
  <proof>
    <p>
      <ol>
        <li>
            <p>
              We  need both <m>A</m> and <m>B</m> to be <m>m\times n </m> for the expression to make sense. It is easy to see that <m>A+B</m> and <m>B+A</m> are both <m>m\times n</m> matrices. We must show <m>(A+B)_{ij}=(B+A)_{ij}</m> for all <m>1\leq i\leq m</m>, <m>1\leq j\leq n</m>. We have
              <md>
                <mrow>(A+B)_{ij} \amp =(A)_{ij}+(B)_{ij}\amp (<xref ref="d_matrix_add_subtract"/>) </mrow>
                <mrow> \amp =(B)_{ij}+(A)_{ij}\amp \text{(real addition is comm.)} </mrow>
                <mrow>  \amp =(B+A)_{ij} \amp (<xref ref="d_matrix_add_subtract"/> </mrow>
              </md>.
            </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </p>
  </proof>

